@Node "Historia programu" "Track2File.guide/Program history"

  @{b}@{u}Version 1.0  (07.07.95) - recognizes 19 IDs@{uu}@{ub}

  - first release

  @{b}@{u}Version 1.01 (05.08.95) - recognizes 24 IDs@{uu}@{ub}

  Recognizes new headers:
  - TPWM - not recognizes size of crunched file
  - ICE!
  - ATM5
  - GP
  - Dupa - IMP!

  Bugs removed:
  - Track2File didn't load full disk to memory i.e. first and last block
  - in file requester, pressing 'Amiga+L' caused selecting Clear instead
    of Load. Now you can use 'Amiga+O' shortcut for loading files.
  - program should work on all Amigas with MC68000 now, but decrunching
    files from odd address can crash your system.

  @{b}@{u}Version 1.02 (10.09.95) - recognizes 29 IDs@{uu}@{ub}

  Recognizes new headers:
  - Ice!
  - IFT?
  - ViS1 - CrM!
  - ViSL - CrM2

  All xfd libraries were rewritten by me and some new ones were added:
  - Ice!
  - IFT?
  - CRUN
  - LOB
  - XPAC

  @{b}@{u}Version 1.03 (25.09.95) - recognizes 31 IDs@{uu}@{ub}

  Added in preferences option to skip found file (skip file),
  for speed up memory scan.

  Recognizes new headers:
  - ATOM
  - Vic2

  New libraries:
  - ATOM
  - FUCK
  - JR
  - HUFF
  - Vic2

  @{b}@{u}Version 1.04 (04.10.95) - recognizes 35 IDs@{uu}@{ub}

  New headers:
  - $18051973 - CrM2 fake
  - CP
  - LOB
  - VOL1

  New libraries:
  - CP
  - SSUR
  - VDCO
  - VOL1

  @{b}@{u}Version 1.05 (10.11.95) - recognizes 37 IDs@{uu}@{ub}

  Added Abort gadget in information requester.

  New headers:
  - RLE
  - TITS - PP20 fake

  New libraries:
  - RLE
  - CRND

  @{b}@{u}Version 1.10 (01.12.95) - recognizes 56 IDs@{uu}@{ub}

  New version recognizes 56 headers and is about @{b}35% faster!@{ub} to
  previous versions. New memory scan procedure is used. In preferences you
  can select what headers you want to search. Settings can be saved on
  disk. They will be loaded when program runs. To all decrunched and saved
  files comment will be added with information about cruncher type.

  New headers:
  - JR
  - SA
  - SC
  - SF
  - SP
  - SQ
  - CRND
  - Dtpk
  - GC!2
  - GC!3
  - HUF#
  - KDUB
  - MASM
  - MASS
  - pack
  - SFHD
  - SPv3
  - SSUR
  - VDCO

  New libraries:
  - GraftGold_Cruncher
  - KDUB
  - MASM
  - MASS
  - pack
  - SPv3

  @{b}@{u}Version 1.11 (19.12.95) - recognizes 58 IDs@{uu}@{ub}

  In preferences some new gadgets was added: Deep search, Invert, Clear.
  With 'Deep search' option turned off program is about @{b}40%
  faster!@{ub} to previous version.

  New headers:
  - PaK0
  - XP10

  New libraries:
  - PaK0
  - MagneticFields (SF i SQ)

  @{b}@{u}Version 1.12 (07.01.96) - recognizes 60 IDs@{uu}@{ub}

  Comment contains Offset and starting block number of NDOS disk saved in
  this file.

  New headers:
  - ALC0
  - FIRE

  New libraries:
  - ALC0
  - ArcR
  - MagneticFields (SC i SP)
  - XP10

  @{b}@{u}Version 1.13 (21.01.96) - recognizes 63 IDs@{uu}@{ub}

  New headers:
  - BDPI - IMP! fake
  - CHFI - IMP! fake
  - FLT! - IMP! fake

  New libraries:
  - FIRE
  - HUF#

  @{b}@{u}Version 1.14 (06.02.96) - recognizes 67 IDs@{uu}@{ub}

  New headers:
  - BH72 - S404 fake
  - BH73 - S404 fake
  - GP11
  - XPKZ - CrM2 fake

  @{b}@{u}Version 1.15 (16.04.96) - recognizes 72 IDs@{uu}@{ub}

  Added new version of xfd.library, it allows to detect length of
  PowerPacked data file. Detection of 100KB file can take few minutes on
  not expanded Amiga 1200, but is 100% reliable.

  Program correctly detects length of files with TPWM headers.

  New headers:
  - 1AM1
  - 2AM1
  - DHp2
  - FRED - IMP! fake
  - SLAM - S404 fake

  New libraries:
  - 1AM1 i 2AM1
  - DHp2

  @{b}@{u}Version 1.16 (07.05.96) - recognizes 74 IDs@{uu}@{ub}

  All xfdmaster.library libraries were corrected to work in multitasking.

  New headers:
  - RNC0
  - TSM!

  @{b}@{u}Version 1.17 (15.07.96) - recognizes 77 IDs@{uu}@{ub}

  New headers:
  - CMP1
  - S300
  - Taz! - ICE! fake

  New libraries:
  - TSM!

@EndNode

@Node "Od autora" "Track2File.guide/From author"

  Track2File is written in assembly language using Devpac v3.14. It
  was tested on Amiga 1200 + Blizzard IV 50 MHz + 8 MB Fast Ram + 540 MB
  Conner HDD.

  If you have any ideas or you have found any bugs, write to me on address:

  Mr. Larmer of Wanted Team
        Czeslaw Maron
      ul.sw.Anny 45/17
      42-700 Lubliniec
           POLAND

   tel. +48 (0-34) 53-04-21

@EndNode

@Node "Disk Read" "Track2File.guide/Disk Read"

  Disk Read

  Reads disk to memory.

@EndNode

@Node "Load File" "Track2File.guide/Load File"

  Load File

  Opens file requester. After selecting file name, loads it to memory.

@EndNode

@Node "Search" "Track2File.guide/Search"

  Search

  Scans allocated memory.  If file header is found requester with
  information about this file opens.  Then you can select:

 @{"Save file      " Link "Save file"}

 @{"Decrunch & save" Link "Decrunch & save"}

 @{"Abort          " Link "Abort"}

 @{"Continue       " Link "Continue"}

@EndNode

@Node "Prefs" "Track2File.guide/Prefs"

  Prefs

  Opens window with program preferences:

 @{"Drive to read       " Link "Drive to read"}
 @{"Inc file name       " Link "Inc file name"}
 @{"Decrunch before save" Link "Decrunch before save"}
 @{"Skip file           " Link "Skip file"}
 @{"Deep search         " Link "Deep search"}
 @{"Save image          " Link "Save image"}
 @{"Enable/Disable IDs  " Link "Enable-Disable IDs"}
 @{"Invert              " Link "Invert"}
 @{"Clear               " Link "Clear"}
 @{"Save                " Link "Save"}
 @{"Use                 " Link "Use"}
 @{"Cancel              " Link "Cancel"}

@EndNode

@Node "Save file" "Track2File.guide/Save file"

  Save file

  Opens file requester and saves file with given file name.

@EndNode

@Node "Decrunch & save" "Track2File.guide/Decrunch & save"

  Decrunch & save

  Decrunches file and opens file requester, then saves decrunched data.

@EndNode

@Node "Abort" "Track2File.guide/Abort"

  Abort

  Aborts memory scan.

@EndNode

@Node "Continue" "Track2File.guide/Continue"

  Continue

  Resumes memory scanning.

@EndNode

@Node "Drive to read" "Track2File.guide/Drive to read"

  Disk read in drive

  Changes drive to read from.

@EndNode

@Node "Inc file name" "Track2File.guide/Inc file name"

  Inc file name

  If this gadget is activated, then after selecting 'Search' and memory
  scanning program will open file requester instead of information window.
  After entering file name, program will write found data and resume
  memory scanning. Program will append an three digit extension to
  file name, eg. if you enter file name Data, program will save files with
  names: Data.001, Data.002, etc...

@EndNode

@Node "Decrunch before save" "Track2File.guide/Decrunch before save"

  Decrunch before save

  The same as 'Inc file name', but files will be decrunched before save.

@EndNode

@Node "Skip file" "Track2File.guide/Skip file"

  Skip file

  After finding file program while resume searching from end of this file.
  If this option is disabled program while search whole this file.

@EndNode

@Node "Deep search" "Track2File.guide/Deep search"

  Deep search

  With this option turned off program scans memory by word (2 bytes), with
  turned on byte by byte.

@EndNode

@Node "Save image" "Track2File.guide/Save image"

  Save image

  Opens file requester. After selecting file name writes loaded data from
  disk to file.

@EndNode

@Node "Enable-Disable IDs" "Track2File.guide/Enable-Disable IDs"

  Enable/Disable IDs

  You can select what headers program should search.

@EndNode

@Node "Invert" "Track2File.guide/Invert"

  Invert

  Inverts selection of headers in 'Enable/Disable IDs' gadget.

@EndNode

@Node "Clear" "Track2File.guide/Clear"

  Clear

  Clears selection of headers in 'Enable/Disable IDs' gadget.

@EndNode

@Node "Save" "Track2File.guide/Save"

  Save

  Saves settings in "s:Track2File.prefs".

@EndNode

@Node "Use" "Track2File.guide/Use"

  Use

  Remebers settings.

@EndNode

@Node "Cancel" "Track2File.guide/Cancel"

  Cancel

  Returns previous settings.

@EndNode
